From: Chad Monroe <chad@monroe.io>
Date: Sun, 15 Feb 2026 12:07:34 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: use only last_rx for AP mode station inactivity

802.11 ACKs are address-based, not association-based. A station that
has roamed to another AP but remains in radio range will still ACK
frames from the old AP, keeping last_ack fresh and preventing
inactivity timeout from ever firing.

Signed-off-by: Chad Monroe <chad@monroe.io>
---
 net/mac80211/sta_info.c |    8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

--- a/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
@@ -3316,6 +3316,14 @@ unsigned long ieee80211_sta_last_active(
 		link_sta_info = wiphy_dereference(sta->local->hw.wiphy,
 						  sta->link[link_id]);
 
+	/* In AP mode, only consider actual received frames for inactivity.
+	 * TX ACKs are RA-based at the 802.11 MAC layer, so a station that
+	 * has roamed to another AP but is still in radio range will continue
+	 * to ACK our frames -- this does not indicate association. */
+	if (sta->sdata->vif.type == NL80211_IFTYPE_AP ||
+	    sta->sdata->vif.type == NL80211_IFTYPE_AP_VLAN)
+		return stats->last_rx;
+
 	if (!link_sta_info->status_stats.last_ack ||
 	    time_after(stats->last_rx, link_sta_info->status_stats.last_ack))
 		return stats->last_rx;
